Text.Value: Before you go in, one last matter, my fetching felon.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Butler looks at you up and down.
EditorData.NodeContext: The butler pauses for a moment,  looking at you up and down

Text.Value: Ah, I am Sceleritas Fel: Butler of Bhaal. I live to die, and die to serve.
Don't lift a pinkie! I have been waiting to open the door for you.
Please bring forth the bearer of the Urge. Then we may all feast our eyes ogling their triumphs.
But I believe in you, now and ever-after.
I see you are dressed in my raiment.
*You have Knocked but only a chill answered. The door is open.*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Knock functionality is removed for now. But could be put back in if needed. 03-03-2023

Text.Value: *The amulet is gone from your possessions. You shall live another day.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [PLYR] presses the Bhaal Amulet into the door.<CodyM>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player presses the Bhaal Amulet into the door.

Text.Value: Oh, Master, Master, MASTER! You have come home to your royal dwelling!
Attack.
I've come to kill Orin, and I'll kill you if you get in my way.
The Temple is all tidied and ready for your worshipful act of mortal combat!
Please go in, my Liege! And take care to watch your step!
*With Gortash dead, Orin awaits you in the Temple's nauseating sanctum.*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Ability to open the door by killing Gortash was removed after a flow review. 09-03-2023

Text.Value: A thousand succubae could give me no greater delight!
Unless Bhaal's true issue is brought before me, I shall not open the door. But you can bring them hither, can't you?
Who or what are you?!
*You do not discover truth, in these symbols you see only death.*
Can you open the door for me?
Don't go, Master! Please... don't go.
Let's face facts, Master, you might never be.
I'm ever so saddened to hear of the trifling little bit of - pardon me - idiocy - that has been imposed upon your poor brain.
The royal Itch, the regal Tingle, the unending Thirst. Oh, I adore them so.
We can play this game for as long as you wish. But please don't kill me again: I feel a blushing adulterer when I am not dying by Master's hand.
You've seen Orin?
Brute! It is your ally's destiny: the Chosen of Bhaal must kill their sibling. If your friend does not kill Orin, oh- don't even make me think of it! It's too sad.
*Bhaal wants only blood.*
I'll be back with the Urge.
Utter a quick prayer to Bhaal.
I wish to enter in fear, and worship the Lord in his sanctum.
Gods, are you the reason my friend is acting so strangely?
If you don't bring the Master soon, I'll put you on Slayer toenail clipping duties for a month.
You do not know Sceleritas. I get killed for fun.
It is an honour that brings a weensy tear to Sceleritas' eye.
But why did you exert yourself so getting here? I was waiting to open the door.
There's a puddle of blood on the floor as you walk in, careful, don't slip!
Although on this eve, I am rather the Doorbeast of Bhaal. I am getting anxious that my Liege is not here yet.
No! Don't leave me to pine!
Lady Orin told me not to let you in, but I'd never listen to the pretender to your fetid throne.
You truly are the wickeder sibling! I shall be punished for allowing your improper dress, I fear it already!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Dark Urge has the standard idle animation where they have their arms folded, looking cocky.

Text.Value: One with such base manners as you is certainly unwelcome in my Liege's home.
I think that Bhaalspawn is one of my companions.
I've got the amulet, just move aside.
Kindly assist the Master in returning home.
You should take it off, though. It would be improper to meet Lord Bhaal in the garb of a lowly servant.
Very good. Every effort should be expended to make a good impression.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Cuts to the Butler, the Dark Urge will JUST end up having their hat off once gameplay starts, don't need to show the DU taking it off.

Text.Value: If the latter, you are tardy. I've done all the work myself. Just go and fetch our honoured Bhaalspawn.
I confess that the last time I came here, I thought it would be my tomb. You can see why.
This Temple awaits the return of its true Master. A fellow of exceptional sin.
*A chill draught strikes as you turn, as if distant eyes were set watching.*
*Murder, bloody murder. Who else but Bhaal would these symbols honour?*
Have you no shame nor manners? This door will open only for one grafted from Bhaalian seed.
I'm the son of Bhaal, I do as I please!
I'm the daughter of Bhaal, I do as I please!
I'm the child of Bhaal, I do as I please!
O, hail, brother, sister, or fellow bosom-cultist.
No loitering, no lollygagging, and no trespassing. This is a private estate.

EditorData.logicalname: PLAYER IS NOT DU BUT DU EXISTS

Text.Value: Your friend is special, ingrate, and you should consider yourself the luckiest wretch in the realms to travel with them.
Hnhgh. I wish I had the honour you did of walking toe to toe, always on the very ground itself the Master treads on.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quite into the idea of the ground the master walks on

Text.Value: Just as I held the victim's nethers for your first castration, selected the scalpel for your first eye-gouging, and seasoned the first man you cooked alive, I will take care of you now.
What were you doing this whole time?
I would have told you, but didn't dream of interrupting when you were enjoying yourself so!
Oh, you simply must go into the Temple, you must! My pattering heart cannot take it any longer!
Being killed by you is so much more pleasurable, Master.
*The Bhaal Amulet trembles in frightened awe.*
Leave.
*Stone seals this chamber against the world.*
I'm not ready to go into the Temple yet.
I've re-stacked every pile of skulls, and mounted more skeletons on the walls for a cosy touch.
Oh, you must be more of our dire Liege's servants. You are dressed in attire demonstrating your respect for the Master.
The eye sockets of our graven god's icon are all polished up, ready to glow menacingly as you bludgeon your sister to death.
Lady Orin told me to allow your passage, but if she hadn't I would have been naughty and slipped you inside anyway.
And in you, I detect scant evil seed.
*No key, no handle. Better to forget. Better to live.*
Who in the Nine Hells are you?
But why come to the Master's estate without them? Have you abandoned them? Or are you here to help with the skull-stacking and corpse-mounting?
Out of the way, creature.
Sceleritas Fel, at your service. A shame our paths have not crossed before, my Master, but now we need never part again.
Ooo, if you dare rob Master of their birthright, you will have Bhaal to answer to! As genocidal maniacs go, he is not the nicest!

EditorData.logicalname: OPENED DOOR AND BUTLER STILL THERE

Text.Value: This is a foul place, better buried. Already Boo is bristling - and not from the cold.

EditorData.NodeContext: Growlingly unhappy to be back here

Text.Value: The hat stays on.
Walk away.
*Will you return, once you cross this threshold?*
Examine the door.
*Bhaal cares not for your empty words.*
Eeek! Of course! Wear what you will.
Bashing the Hollyphant's wormy trunk was a particularly refined deed.
I'll take it off before I go in.
Open it!
While I would love naught more than to join you in worship, Lord Bhaal requires your aid in another way first.
Press the Amulet against the door.
Every day she kills me as I'm trying to beautify the Temple for your return. Up to thrice, some days.
But it belongs to Orin: she wishes to see me.
We are unfortunate bunkmates, as she refuses to leave your estate!
I went through the whole tribunal when you could have opened the door?!
Oh, I jest. I enjoy grooming the beast far too much to let you lay a hand on it.
How dare you so much as whisper the name of that serf, that watery-blooded peasant who pretends to bear the Lord's name?

Synopsis:
The Bhaal Temple is closed off by a massive door. They are 3 ways to open the door.
1) with an Bhaal Amulet, given in the Serial Killer situation
2) with invitation from Orin - which is given when players killed Gortash, after she has given the players the ultimatum
3) if players are the Dark Urge, their butler will freely open the doors for the players.
